headline: Dominion Energy's 88% Data Center Demand Spike Could Get the Dividend Growing Again
summary: Dominion Energy (NYSE: D) is one of the largest regulated utilities in the United States.  At the moment, it's offering a lofty 4.8% dividend yield at a time when the average utility's yield is just 2.8%.  News last month of an 88% spike in demand for energy from data centers could help get this high-yield stock back on its dividend feet.
